{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/14013", "id": 15585591, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MTU1ODU1OTE=", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/14013", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/14013.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/14013.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/14013", "number": 14013, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "libterm: Use Windows Console API to color texts.", "user": {"login": "ghost", "id": 10137, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMTM3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10137?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost", "html_url": "https://github.com/ghost", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "This patch adds the coloring function on Windows console to libterm.\nFixes #13400, and makes working on MSYS slightly more pleasant.\n\n_Quick Notes_\n- Extract `trait TerminalOps<T>` from `Terminal<T>`.\n- Add `struct WindowsConsole<T>` along with `Terminal<T>`, both implements `TerminalOps<T>`.\n- `term::Terminal::new` is now `term::new_terminal`, returns `~TerminalOps<T>`.\n- Windows-specific code, including `WindowsConsole<T>`, is in the module `windows`.\n- It will assume it's running on terminal that understands ASCII if $TERM is \"xterm\". Attempts to not break rxvt.exe.\n- It spams `:Send` to deal with libsyntax, which packs Terminal into a RefCell. I couldn't come up with any smarter fix.\n\nI had to remove `Terminal::unwrap()` to implement `Drop` on `WindowsConsole<T>`, thus it lose the way to manually destroy itself. I suppose it's okay, since I couldn't find any use of it in the tree.\nAlso, it will not be possible to access the members of `Terminal<T>`, such as TermInfo. It's still possible to see terminfo by calling `term::terminfo::parser::compiled::parse`, though.\n\nAs this is Windows-only improvement, I'm not sure about breaking change is acceptable. I can consider more humble way to do this, if it doesn't pay.\n", "created_at": "2014-05-07T09:29:53Z", "updated_at": "2014-06-21T14:51:58Z", "closed_at": "2014-05-07T15:22:06Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "47aaa86f5b35eb826faa2c625e86266866ef0a31", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/14013/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/14013/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/14013/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/statuses/da80d192348d3a231d373966b5e472fb85c3c632", "head": {"label": null, "ref": "libterm-windows", "sha": "da80d192348d3a231d373966b5e472fb85c3c632", "user": null, "repo": null}, "base": {"label": "rust-lang:master", "ref": "master", "sha": "2dcbad5bc40b3ef7d1150db12fba1d653b1c3b16", "user": {"login": "rust-lang", "id": 5430905, "node_id": "MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjU0MzA5MDU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5430905?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rust-lang", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang", "followers_url": "